{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 271 "3.  Fundamental Theorem of Algebra.  The
 Fundamental Theorem of Algebra asserts that every non-constant polyno
mial (with complex-valued coefficients) has a root (a zero, a solution
).  A consequence of the Fundamental Theorem of Algebra is that every \+
polynomial of degree " }{TEXT 276 1 "n" }{TEXT -1 13 " has exactly " }
{TEXT 277 1 "n" }{TEXT -1 108 " roots.  An alternate formulation of th
is consequence would be that every non-constant polynomial of degree \+
" }{TEXT 279 1 "n" }{TEXT -1 38 " can be factored into a product of a \+
 " }{TEXT 278 1 "n" }{TEXT -1 16 " linear factors." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 35 "Consider the following po
lynomials:" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 
-1 6 "I.    " }{XPPEDIT 19 1 "f := x^3-x^2-2*x" "6#>%\"fG,(*$%\"xG\"\"
$\"\"\"*$F'\"\"#!\"\"*&F+F)F'F)F," }{TEXT -1 15 "         II.   " }
{XPPEDIT 19 1 "g := 6*x^3+11*x^2+6*x+1" "6#>%\"gG,**&\"\"'\"\"\"*$%\"x
G\"\"$F(F(*&\"#6F(*$F*\"\"#F(F(*&F'F(F*F(F(F(F(" }{TEXT -1 24 "       \+
          III.   " }{XPPEDIT 19 1 "h := x^3-5*x+x^2-5;" "6#>%\"hG,**$%
\"xG\"\"$\"\"\"*&\"\"&F)F'F)!\"\"*$F'\"\"#F)F+F," }{TEXT -1 19 "      \+
             " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 7 "IV.    " }{XPPEDIT 19 1 "
F := x^4-144" "6#>%\"FG,&*$%\"xG\"\"%\"\"\"\"$W\"!\"\"" }{TEXT -1 19 "
             V.    " }{XPPEDIT 19 1 "G := 3*x^4+4*x^3-2*x^2+x-6;" "6#>
%\"GG,,*&\"\"$\"\"\"*$%\"xG\"\"%F(F(*&F+F(*$F*F'F(F(*&\"\"#F(*$F*F/F(!
\"\"F*F(\"\"'F1" }{TEXT -1 15 "         VI.   " }{XPPEDIT 19 1 "H := x
